6. STOREFRONT - Checkout
================================================================================
File: public/checkout.php

WORKFLOW:
1. Guest checkout: /checkout.php?guest=1 (minimal form, session cart)
2. Signed-in checkout: full customer details, saved payment methods

STEP-BY-STEP:
1. Shipping address form displayed
   - Signed-in: pre-populated from user profile
   - Guest: blank form
2. Shipping method selection (pickup or delivery)
   - Same zone/cost calculation as cart page
   - Address determines zone dynamically
3. Tax calculation:
   - Based on delivery address zip code
   - Looked up from tax_rates table by zip
   - Non-taxable items excluded (services)
4. Payment selection:
   a. Client card: if client-billable and client has linked payment method
   b. User saved cards: dropdown of saved payment methods
   c. Stripe payment element: new card entry via Stripe Elements
   d. Pay by Invoice: shown when vendor's client has allowInvoice=1
      - Skips Stripe, creates order with paymentMethod='invoice'
      - Auto-generates PDF invoice and emails it to user
5. Promo code input (optional):
   - Validates against promotions table
   - Applies discount to order
6. Billing address: same as shipping toggle, or separate form
7. Order review: shows all items, subtotal, tax, shipping, total
8. Accounting validation: ensures assignments sum = item quantities
9. "Place Order" button:
   a. Form submitted with all data
   b. Server calls site_place_order(data)
   c. Payment processed via Stripe (or client card, or invoice)
   d. Order created in orders table
   e. Order items inserted in order_items table
   f. Inventory decremented via site_reduce_inventory()
   g. Accounting copied from cart to order
   h. Cart cleared
   i. Order confirmation email sent
   j. Admin notification email sent
   k. Redirect to order confirmation page
10. Remember-me uses site_remember_me() function (sets cookie params before session start)

