48. ADMIN - Manual Stripe Charge
================================================================================
File: public/admin-charge.php

REQUIRES: admin or manager role (opd_require_role)

WORKFLOW:
1. Admin enters customer email in search form (GET request)
2. Server looks up user by email in users table
3. If found: loads saved Stripe payment methods (stripePaymentMethodId IS NOT NULL)
4. If not found: shows "No user found for that email" error
5. If user has no Stripe cards: shows "No Stripe cards saved" message

CHARGE WORKFLOW:
1. Admin selects saved card from dropdown
   - Cards displayed as: "{brand} ending {last4}" or custom label
2. Enters charge amount (USD, min $0.50)
3. Enters currency code (default: usd, 3-letter validation)
4. Optionally links to an Order ID
5. Enters charge reference (required, used for idempotency key)
6. POST action=charge with CSRF token
7. Server validates:
   a. User and payment method exist
   b. Amount is positive and numeric
   c. Currency is valid 3-letter code
   d. Charge reference is not empty
8. Creates Stripe customer if needed via stripe_get_or_create_customer()
9. Calls stripe_create_payment_intent() with:
   - Customer ID, payment method, amount in cents
   - Idempotency key: "manual-charge-{reference}"
   - Metadata: orderId, userId, localPaymentMethodId, chargeReference, initiatedBy
10. On success:
    a. Inserts payment record in payments table (id, orderId, method, externalId, amount, status)
    b. If orderId provided: updates orders.paymentStatus to 'paid' (if succeeded)
    c. Shows "Charge succeeded" or "Charge created with status: {status}"
11. On failure: shows Stripe error message

UI:
- OPD Admin branded header with "Admin Command" / "Manual Stripe Charge"
- "Back to Admin" and "Logout" links in top bar
- Two-form layout: search form (GET) + charge form (POST)
- Success/error message banner

