56. BACKEND - Guest Registration (Bot Protection)
================================================================================
File: api/guest_register.php

NOTE: Section 8 documents the standard customer registration via login.php.
This section documents the separate guest-to-account conversion API endpoint.

WORKFLOW:
1. POST only, CSRF required
2. Parses JSON body
3. Bot protection checks:
   a. Honeypot field (website_url): must be empty (bots auto-fill hidden fields)
   b. Form load timestamp (_fts): checked via site_check_bot()
      - Rejects submissions too fast (bot speed) or too old
4. Validates required fields:
   a. Email: must be valid format
   b. Password: validated via opd_validate_password() (strength rules)
   c. Name: sanitized via opd_sanitize_name()
5. Checks email uniqueness in users table
6. Records registration attempt for rate limiting via site_record_registration_attempt()
7. Creates user:
   a. Generates ID with 'usr' prefix
   b. Hashes password with PASSWORD_DEFAULT (bcrypt)
   c. Sets role='customer', status='active'
8. Auto-login: sets session with site_user key
9. Returns JSON: {ok: true, userId, redirect: '/dashboard.php'}

DIFFERENCES FROM STANDARD REGISTER (Section 8):
- API-only endpoint (JSON request/response, no HTML form)
- Additional bot protection (honeypot + timestamp)
- No welcome email sent
- No pending invitation linking
- Designed for guest checkout -> account conversion flow

