57. BACKEND - Order Cancellation Inventory Return
================================================================================
File: api/orders.php (pre-CRUD hook, lines 342-374)

NOTE: Section 26 documents refund-based inventory return. This section documents
the automatic inventory return when an order status is changed to "Cancelled".

WORKFLOW:
1. Admin updates order status to "Cancelled" via PUT /api/orders.php
2. Before the standard CRUD update, a pre-hook intercepts:
   a. Checks if new status is "Cancelled"
   b. Checks if order is NOT already "Cancelled" (prevents double-return)
3. Loads all order_items for the order (productId, variantId, quantity)
4. For each item with quantity > 0:
   a. If variantId present: UPDATE product_variants SET inventory = inventory + qty
   b. Else if productId present: UPDATE products SET inventory = inventory + qty
   c. Sets updatedAt timestamp on the inventory record
5. Standard CRUD update then proceeds (sets order status to Cancelled)

KEY DIFFERENCES FROM REFUND INVENTORY RETURN:
- Automatic: no "Return to Inventory" checkbox needed
- Returns ALL items: no per-item quantity selection
- No Stripe refund: only inventory is restored, no payment reversal
- Idempotent: double-cancel does not double-return inventory

